to\'a0click an object, then repeats.\cf9 \cb1 \outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec9   For dragging, even more effort is required of the \
individual hand.\'a0 \
\
Using the mouse is\'a0more taxing than it appears\'a0because it is not set up like\
musical instruments that divide the roles and provide balanced interaction.\'a0\
Important to mention, just one\'a0person contributed to the mouse, Douglas Engelbart,\'a0\
and it hasn't received\'a0fundamental upgrades since its\'a0introduction in 1968.\'a0\'a0\
\cf9 \cb10 \strokec9 Our bimodal/dual-input theory addresses its main discomfort, what induces complaints\
from people who work with the mouse all day and sometimes even require wrist\
support\cf9 \cb1 \strokec9 .\'a0 You can experience how Noctivagous reconfigures the mouse by\
trying out the vector-drawing demonstration on this web page
